plicitly show feedforward propagation\n- Score: null\n\n**14. Feedforward AMPA** - Fast excitatory drive via AMPA receptors\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**15. Feedforward NMDA** - Voltage-dependent amplification of error signals\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**16. Feedforward Ascending Gamma** - Rhythmic synchronization (30-90Hz) for feedforward transmission\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**17. Feedforward Specific Error** - Functional requirement that error signal is strictly feedforward-directed\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**18. Supragranular Activity (L2/3)** - Localization of error-signaling neurons in Layers 2/3\n- The study uses fMRI and scalp ERPs, not laminar recordings\n- Score: null\n\n**19. Granular Activity (L4)** - Arrival of prediction error signals in Layer 4\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**20. Feedforward Directed Connectivity** - Directional measures confirming feedforward propagation\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**21. Feedforward Activation** - Functional activation patterns tracing feedforward propagation\n- The study shows activation in auditory cortex for local effects and distributed network for global effects\n- But doesn\'t trace feedforward propagation specifically\n- Score: null\n\n**22. Ascending Latency Shift** - Systematic increases in response latency characterizing feedforward propagation\n- The study shows temporal differences between local (130-300ms) and global (260ms+) effects\n- But this is not explicitly feedforward propagation through hierarchy\n- Score: null\n\n**23. Feedforward Error Propagation** - Explicit evidence that prediction error is transmitted via feedforward pathways\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n**24. Subcortical Feedforward Relaying** - Relaying of prediction error by subcortical structures\n- Not addressed\n- Score: null\n\n## H3: Ubiquity (IDs 25-36)\n\n**25. Canonical Microcircuit Ubiquity** - Ubiquitous presence of L2/3 Error and L5/6 Prediction motif\n- Not addressed\n- S