he paper focuses on feedback (top-down) error propagation, not feedforward. Score: null (not directly addressed)\n\n24. **Subcortical Feedforward Relaying** - The paper mentions thalamocortical projections but doesn\'t discuss subcortical relaying of prediction error. Score: null (not addressed)\n\n## H3: Ubiquity (IDs 25-36)\n\n25. **Canonical Microcircuit Ubiquity** - The paper discusses a canonical microcircuit motif (L2/3 Error and L5/6 Prediction) but doesn\'t explicitly claim it repeats across all levels. Score: null (not directly addressed)\n\n26. **Hierarchical Mechanism Invariance** - The paper shows the mechanism works across hierarchical levels (input, hidden, output), suggesting invariance. Score: 0.6 (moderate evidence - demonstrated across levels)\n\n27. **Hierarchical Activity Ubiquity** - The paper shows prediction-error activity (burst probability changes) across hierarchical levels. Score: 0.6 (moderate evidence - demonstrated across levels)\n\n28. **Hierarchical CSD Ubiquity** - The paper doesn\'t discuss current source density profiles. Score: null (not addressed)\n\n29. **Cross-Scale Hierarchical Ubiquity** - The paper uses both spiking simulations and rate models, showing effects across scales. Score: 0.6 (moderate evidence - demonstrated at multiple scales)\n\n30. **Hierarchical Presence (V1-PFC)** - The paper doesn\'t specifically address V1, V4, PFC areas. Score: null (not addressed)\n\n31. **Cross-Modal Ubiquity** - The paper focuses on visual (image classification) tasks, not multiple modalities. Score: null (not addressed)\n\n32. **Interspecies Hierarchical Ubiquity** - The paper doesn\'t compare across species. Score: null (not addressed)\n\n33. **Temporal Stability of Ubiquity** - The paper shows consistent mechanisms across learning sessions, but not specifically temporal stability. Score: null (not directly addressed)\n\n34. **Hierarchical Order Stability** - The paper shows the mechanism works across the hierarchy, not localized to a